{{infobox deity| member_of= {{ill|17 spirits of the world|simple|User:Immanuelle/17 spirits of the world|ja|十七世神|fr|User:Immanuelle/17 esprits du monde|12=draft|12=draft}} | type = Shinto | children = | father = | consort = | mother = | Name = Yashimamujinokami | Predecessor = | Successor = | Divine Order = {{ill|Kunitsukami|ja|国津神|12=draft|12=draft}} | Full Name = 八島牟遅能神 (Yashimamujinokami) | Alternate Name= 八嶋牟遅能神 | Other Names = | Divine Rank = | Divine Role = God of the Land | Mausoleum = | Father = Unknown | Mother = | Relatives = | Consort = Unknown | Children = {{ill|Tottorijin|ja|鳥取神|12=draft|12=draft}} | Shrine = | Texts = {{ill|Kojiki|ja|古事記|12=draft|12=draft}} }}
'''Yashimamujinokami''' (八島牟遅能神, {{smaller|Modern kana orthography:}} ヤシマムジ) is a deity appearing in {{ill|Japanese mythology|ja|日本神話|12=draft|12=draft}}.
== Overview == Yashimamujinokami is a deity mentioned exclusively in the ''{{ill|Kojiki|ja|古事記|12=draft|12=draft}}'' and is regarded as the parent of {{ill|Tottorijin|ja|鳥取神|12=draft|12=draft}}.
The name "Yashima" means "many islands," while "Muji" denotes "noble person." "No" is interpreted as a case particle, giving the name the meaning of "Noble person of many islands."{{Sfn|Nishinomiya|2014|p=381}}
== Genealogy == [[File:Ohokuninushi family tree.png|right|thumb|250px|Genealogy of Ōkuninushi (as per the ''Kojiki''). Blue represents male deities, red represents female deities, and yellow represents deities of unknown gender.]]
Yashimamujinokami's daughter is Tottorijin, who bore {{ill|Torinarumi no Kami|ja|鳥鳴海神|1=Torinarumi-no-Kami|1=Torinarumi-no-Kami|12=draft|12=draft}} with {{ill|Ōkuninushi|ja|大国主神|12=draft|12=draft}}.
